    <!-- Solar Planning Specific -->
    <string name="solar_help_title">Solar Planning Help</string>
    <string name="solar_help_description">This tool helps you design an optimal solar system based on your electricity consumption patterns and local conditions.</string>
    <string name="solar_help_consumption">Daily consumption is your average electricity usage per day. Peak usage is typically during evening hours when electricity rates are highest.</string>
    <string name="solar_help_panels">Solar panel wattage affects how many panels you need. Higher wattage panels are more efficient but more expensive.</string>
    <string name="solar_help_battery">Battery capacity determines how much energy you can store for use when the sun isn\'t shining. Depth of discharge affects battery lifespan.</string>
    <string name="solar_help_efficiency">System efficiency accounts for losses in inverters, wiring, and temperature effects.</string>
    <string name="solar_help_sun_hours">Sun hours vary by location and season. More sun hours mean more production.</string>
    <string name="solar_help_grid_dependency">Grid dependency shows how much you still rely on the grid. Lower is better for energy independence.</string>
    <string name="solar_help_roi">Return on investment shows how quickly you\'ll recoup your initial investment.</string>
    
